snippet: The protracted distribution negotiations under way between Dish Network and the Walt Disney Company are said to focus on digital rights like ad-skipping and online streaming.
abstract: Protracted distribution negotiations under way between Dish Network and Walt Disney Company continue, with no new deal in sight, more than one month after sweeping distribution deal expired; main issues are said to focused on digital rights like ad-skipping and online streaming.
lead_paragraph: The protracted distribution negotiations under way between Dish Network and the Walt Disney Company are said to focus on digital rights like ad-skipping and online streaming.

headline.main: Disney and Dish Wrangle Not Over Broadcast Fees, but the Future of TV
headline.print_headline: Disney and Dish Wrangle Not Over Broadcast Fees, But the Future of TV
